  "unit": {
    "n": 2,
    "lang": "ar",
    "title": "من أنا؟",
    "sub": "Self-introduction",
    "icon": "📛",
    "level": "A1.1",
    "color": "#D4A017",
    "objectives": [
      "ok_introduce_self",
      "ok_how_are_you"
    ]
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "aru2l1",
      "title": "اسمي... 📛",
      "xp": 20,
      "steps": [
        {
          "type": "intro",
          "title": "My Name Is... 📛",
          "desc": "Introduce yourself in Arabic — names, origins, and the essential question words.",
          "goals": [
            "'My name is...'",
            "'I am from...'",
            "How are you?"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "اسمي",
          "en": "My name is...",
          "img": "📛✨",
          "phonetic": "IS-mee",
          "example": "اسمي أحمد. وأنت؟",
          "exampleEn": "My name is Ahmed. And you?",
          "note": "'اسم' (ism) = name. The 'ي' (ee) at the end = my. So 'اسمي' = 'my name'. Arabic builds meaning through suffixes!",
          "kind": "grammar"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "أنا من",
          "en": "I am from...",
          "img": "🌍✈️",
          "phonetic": "A-na min",
          "example": "أنا من مصر",
          "exampleEn": "I am from Egypt.",
          "note": "'أنا' = I, 'من' = from. Arabic has NO verb 'to be' in present tense! 'أنا من مصر' literally = 'I from Egypt'.",
          "kind": "grammar"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "كيف حالك؟",
          "en": "How are you?",
          "img": "💬❤️",
          "phonetic": "KAY-fa HAA-lak",
          "example": "مرحبا! كيف حالك؟",
          "exampleEn": "Hello! How are you?",
          "note": "Literally 'How is your condition?' Reply: 'بخير، شكرا' = Fine, thanks. Or 'الحمد لله' = Praise be to God — the most common reply.",
          "kind": "phrase"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "أنا بخير",
          "en": "I'm fine",
          "img": "😊👍",
          "phonetic": "A-na bi-KHAYR",
          "example": "أنا بخير، الحمد لله",
          "exampleEn": "I'm fine, praise God.",
          "note": "Adding 'الحمد لله' is extremely common — it's a cultural expression, not just religious.",
          "kind": "phrase"
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "title": "🚫 No 'To Be' in Arabic!",
          "text": "Arabic has NO present tense of 'to be':\n\n• أنا أحمد = I [am] Ahmed\n• أنا من مصر = I [am] from Egypt\n• أنا بخير = I [am] fine\n• هذا كتاب = This [is] a book\n\nNo conjugation, no 'am/is/are'. Just put words together!\nThis is one of the EASIEST parts of Arabic grammar."
        },
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "q": "'أنا من مصر' means:",
          "opts": [
            "I speak Egyptian",
            "My name is Egypt",
            "I am from Egypt",
            "I love Egypt"
          ],
          "ans": "I am from Egypt",
          "hint": "أنا = I, من = from, مصر = Egypt"
        },
        {
          "type": "tr",
          "mk": "ar_my_name",
          "dir": "comprehend"
        },
        {
          "type": "tr",
          "mk": "ar_how_are_you",
          "dir": "comprehend"
        },
        {
          "type": "match",
          "mks": [
            "ar_my_name",
            "ar_from",
            "ar_how_are_you",
            "ar_fine"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "aru2l2",
      "title": "نعم ولا ✅❌",
      "xp": 20,
      "steps": [
        {
          "type": "intro",
          "title": "Yes, No & Essentials ✅❌",
          "desc": "The most important tiny words plus basic nouns.",
          "goals": [
            "Yes/No",
            "Sorry",
            "Basic nouns"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "نعم",
          "en": "Yes",
          "img": "✅👍",
          "phonetic": "NA-am",
          "example": "نعم، أنا من هنا",
          "exampleEn": "Yes, I am from here.",
          "note": "Formal 'yes'. Casual: 'أيوا' (aywa) or 'إيه' (eeh).",
          "kind": "word"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "لا",
          "en": "No",
          "img": "❌🙅",
          "phonetic": "laa",
          "example": "لا، شكرا",
          "exampleEn": "No, thank you.",
          "note": "The long 'aa' is important. 'لا شكرا' = no thank you (perfectly polite).",
          "kind": "word"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "ماء",
          "en": "water",
          "img": "💧🥤",
          "phonetic": "MAA-a",
          "example": "ماء من فضلك",
          "exampleEn": "Water, please.",
          "note": "Essential survival word! 'ماء بارد' (maa' baarid) = cold water.",
          "kind": "word"
        },
        {
          "type": "teach",
          "nl": "كتاب",
          "en": "book",
          "img": "📖📚",
          "phonetic": "ki-TAAB",
          "example": "هذا كتاب",
          "exampleEn": "This is a book.",
          "note": "From root ك-ت-ب (k-t-b) = writing. كتاب (book), كاتب (writer), مكتب (office), مكتبة (library) — all from 3 letters!",
          "kind": "word"
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "title": "🌳 Arabic Root System",
          "text": "Arabic is built on 3-letter ROOTS:\n\nك-ت-ب (k-t-b) = writing:\n• كتاب = book\n• كاتب = writer\n• مكتب = office/desk\n• مكتبة = library\n\nد-ر-س (d-r-s) = studying:\n• درس = lesson\n• مدرسة = school\n• مدرّس = teacher\n\nOnce you spot roots, vocabulary explodes open!"
        },
        {
          "type": "mc",
          "q": "'لا شكرا' means:",
          "opts": [
            "Yes please",
            "No thank you",
            "You're welcome",
            "Excuse me"
          ],
          "ans": "No thank you",
          "hint": "لا = no, شكرا = thank you"
        },
        {
          "type": "match",
          "mks": [
            "ar_yes",
            "ar_no",
            "ar_water",
            "ar_book"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "tr",
          "mk": "ar_yes",
          "dir": "produce"
        },
        {
          "type": "tr",
          "mk": "ar_sorry",
          "dir": "comprehend"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
